#wrapper(ng-class="{'toggled': menuOpen}")
	#sidebar-wrapper
		ul.sidebar-nav
			li.sidebar-brand 
				a(href='/' target="_self") Back to Site
			li(ng-repeat="state in cmsStates" ui-sref='{{state.name}}' ng-show="state.userHasPermission" ng-click="toggleMenu()")
				i.fa(ng-class="state.icon")
				a {{state.friendlyName}}
	#meanbase-cms
		//- #menu-toggle.btn.btn-default.fa.fa-bars()|  Menu
		nav.navbar-default.navbar-inverse
			.container
				div.navbar-header 
					button.navbar-toggle.collapsed(ng-click="toggleMenu()").pull-left.dont-hide
						span.sr-only Toggle navigation
						span.icon-bar
						span.icon-bar
						span.icon-bar
					.navbar-brand {{pageTitle}}
		div(ui-view="")
			h1 Welcome to meanbase CMS
			p I'm sure your excited and maybe nervous to begin managing your website. Don't worry we've made the process easy to follow. Just start clicking buttons. Just be careful on the theme's page, that could mess up your site.
